&lt;p>The aims of the scheme are to:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>Promote knowledge transfer between academic departments and 'partner organisations' and the staff employed in them&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Provide 'partner organisations' with research-informed evidence to develop and review policy&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Expand networks for 'partner organisations' into academia&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Provide career development opportunities and offer skills updating&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Enable all parties, including ESRC, to develop their understanding of research and policymaking process and the interactions between them.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>This fellowship will involve an ethnographic study of the attitudes, behaviours and wider social impact of veterinary diagnostic technologies. The research will be designed in the first three week of the placement, in conjunction with Defra.&lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-01-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2009-09-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>25303</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs><gtr:collaborationOutput><gtr:collaboratingOrganisation>Fera Science Limited</gtr:collaboratingOrganisation><gtr:country>United Kingdom of Great Britain &amp; Northern Ireland (UK)</gtr:country><gtr:description>Investigating the benefits, costs and barriers to uptake of field diagnostics within the PHSI</gtr:description><gtr:id>F02AE6F1-FA2D-43EB-9107-757925C3BF6A</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>b95824f6b9582514-1</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:piContribution>Collaboration to investigate the use of field-side diagnostics by the Plant Health and Seeds Inspectorate</gtr:piContribution><gtr:sector>Multiple</gtr:sector><gtr:start>2011-01-01</gtr:start></gtr:collaborationOutput></gtr:collaborationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Rapid/point of care diagnostics : exploring attitudes, behaviours &amp; wider social impacts</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:id>C5A7A5D8-4589-4FBB-A8FB-316D39CB149A</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Internal presentation to Defra</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>r-8663988689.5790582b078a6c</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:year>2012</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>A short walk with civil servants : reflections on a placement at Defra</gt